</note><section id="fs-id1312815" class="section-summary"><title>Section Summary</title><list id="fs-id2607618"><item id="import-auto-id3137375">The spreading of white light into its full spectrum of wavelengths is called dispersion. </item>
    <item id="import-auto-id2994679">Rainbows are produced by a combination of refraction and reflection and involve the dispersion of sunlight into a continuous distribution of colors.</item>
    <item id="import-auto-id1536161">Dispersion produces beautiful rainbows but also causes problems in certain optical systems.</item></list></section><section id="fs-id1010697" type="problems-exercises" class="problems-exercises"><title>Problems &amp; Exercises</title><exercise id="fs-id2657132" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2528419">
