    </problem></exercise>
    <exercise id="fs-id2756320" type="problem-exercises"><problem id="fs-id2511903">
    <para id="import-auto-id3107343">(a) A narrow beam of light containing yellow (580 nm) and green (550 nm) wavelengths goes from polystyrene to air, striking the surface at a <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>30</m:mtext><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mn>0º</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math> incident angle. What is the angle between the colors when they emerge? (b) How far would they have to travel to be separated by 1.00 mm?</para></problem>
